node.title: Live - Omicron reaches MIQ: Expert says variant will creep into the community 'eventually'
node.content: ["New Zealand has recorded its first case of Omicron, the recently identified 'variant of concern', in a Christchurch managed isolation facility.", "The person, who travelled from Germany via Dubai and arrived on December 10, is now completing two weeks of isolation at the Sudima Christchurch Airport facility. They are fully vaccinated.\u00a0", "The discovery followed a major milestone for New Zealand - 90 percent of eligible Kiwis are now fully vaccinated against COVID-19. Pfizer-BioNTech's paediatric vaccine was also granted provisional approval by Medsafe for use in children aged five to 11.", "Meanwhile, thousands of people descended on the capital on Thursday for a planned march to Parliament, in\u00a0 in protest of vaccination mandates and ongoing restrictions.\u00a0\n", "7:25am - Kia ora, good morning, and welcome to Newshub's live coverage of the COVID-19 outbreak for Friday, December 17."]
